<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-14T19:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-14T19:30:00-05:00" n="171" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1756</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Continental and Commercial
                                    Trust &amp; Savings Bank</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chicago, Illinois</hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-14T18:30:00-06:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1917, 6.30
                                p.m</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In connection with the loan negotiations which this bank has been
                            conducting with the Republic of China through Minister Koo, we have
                            requested an extention of time until June 15 in which to send our
                            representatives to China to make a full investigation and conduct the
                            negotiations. While we understand Minister Koo has requested the
                            extention we have received no advice that his request has been granted.
                            We would be much pleased if you would take the matter up with the
                            American Minister at Peking and endeavor to secure the extension for
                            us.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur Reynold</hi>, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Vice President</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>